# Content & Data

## Content Files

Markdown with YAML frontmatter in `content/`. Loaded by `src/lib/content.ts`.

- `content/articles/articles.md` — Articles (type: "articles")
- `content/articles/quickBits.md` — Quick Bits (type: "quick-bits")
- `content/speaking/talks.md` — Talks (type: "talks")
- `content/resume/workExperience.md` — Work experience (supports `subEntries` for grouped roles)
- `content/resume/education.md` — Education
- `content/general/copy.md` — Site copy (elevatorPitch, greetingIntro, etc.)
- `content/general/dictionary.md` — UI labels
- `content/general/headings.md` — Section headings
- `content/general/tags.md` — Tag key/value pairs

## Duplicate Slugs

The talks data has duplicate slugs (same talk at different events). `dedupeBySlug()` keeps the most recent. Always deduplicate content to avoid breaking view transitions.

## Markdown Pipeline

`src/lib/markdown.ts`: marked → marked-highlight (highlight.js, Atom One Dark) → `enrichHtml()`.

`src/lib/enrich-html.ts` post-processes HTML:
- External links get `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`
- Images get `loading="lazy"` and `<figure>` wrapping
- YouTube iframes get responsive aspect-ratio containers

## Article Body Fallback

Some talks have `summary` instead of `body`. The Article component falls back: `article.body || article.summary || ""`.

## Friday Tips

`src/lib/youtube.ts` fetches from YouTube API at build time. Requires `YOUTUBE_API_KEY` env var. Returns `[]` without it.
